{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/breaking-prod/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>You <strong>WILL</strong> break production Unless you know these 5 backend dev tips:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Don't run heavy or slow code in a web request, move it to a background job - otherwise requests start piling up and response times tank.</li>\n<li>Train yourself to spot N + 1 queries. They're silent in dev, but under real traffic they hammer your database and kill your performance.</li>\n<li>If you're running an expensive query repeatedly cache the response in an in memory data store like Redis or Memcached. It'll take the pressure off the database and speed up responses.</li>\n<li>Know when to denormalize. If your data's read heavy, optimize for reads, not textbook normalization.</li>\n<li>Make your database migrations reversible. If one of them goes wrong, you'll stall the deployment pipeline and scramble to recover.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Back end isn't just about writing code, it's about not breaking stuff.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 511px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/31b5051039a869264b94491c34b464ca/08128/breaking_prod.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 77.71428571428571%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"breaking prod\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/31b5051039a869264b94491c34b464ca/08128/breaking_prod.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/31b5051039a869264b94491c34b464ca/71299/breaking_prod.jpg 175w,\n/static/31b5051039a869264b94491c34b464ca/1e